uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.stateful

Class FormState

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.AbstractContexed
      • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.stateful.FormState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Contexed

    public class FormState
extends AbstractContexed
    Form state held in the session. This is to implement multi-stage forms built using a single build method. The normal idiom is that the multi-stage form is a single form where sets of inputs are added in stages (being validated and locked on each stage transition) allowing the values chosen in early stages to be used to customise the form contents in later stages.

    • Method Detail

      • poll

        public boolean poll(Form f)
             throws TransitionException
        poll the cached state for the contents of a partially build form. If all the form inputs have values cached in the form state then the form contents will be updated to match.

        If the form validates in the new state:

        • The existing inputs are all locked
        • A reset action is added to clear the cached state
        • The method returns true.
        If the form fails to validate an exception is thrown. It should validate if the form is built consistently as the cached values will have come from a previous iteration.

        If the cached values are not found:

        • A next action is added that will update the cached state. Note that the reset action may also be present if this is not the first stage.
        • The method returns false to indicate to the form building method that form building should stop at this point.
        Parameters:
        f - Form being built
        Returns:
        true/false if form building should continue.
        Throws:
        TransitionException

      • clear

        public void clear()
        Delete all cached state under this name. Normally this should be called as part of the final form action to reset the multi-stage form. Otherwise it will return to the last stage if re-visited.
